    <!-- READINESS SLIDER (COLD WAVES & FLOODS) -->
    <section id="readiness">
      <div class="section-card readiness-card">
        <div class="section-header">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-temperature-low"></i>
          <h2>Get Ready: Cold Waves & Floods</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="readiness-slider">
          <div class="readiness-slide active" id="slide-cold">
            <div class="readiness-content">
              <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-snowflake"></i> Get Ready for Cold Waves</h3>
              <p>
                Severe cold waves can lead to hypothermia, frostbite and
                respiratory problems. Prepare in advance to stay warm and safe.
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Keep enough warm clothes, blankets and socks ready.</li>
                <li>Seal windows and doors to reduce cold air drafts.</li>
                <li>Store basic medicines for cold, fever and cough.</li>
              </ul>
              <button
                type="button"
                class="btn btn-outline read-more-toggle"
                data-target="coldMore"
              >
                Read more
              </button>
              <div class="read-more-content" id="coldMore">
                <p>
                  • Avoid prolonged exposure to cold; wear layers instead of a single thick jacket.<br />
                  • Keep a hot water bottle or heating pad (use carefully) for elderly and infants.<br />
                  • Ensure proper ventilation if you are using room heaters to avoid carbon monoxide build-up.<br />
                  • Check on neighbours, especially elderly or people living alone, during extreme cold.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="readiness-image-box">
              <!-- Cold wave image -->
              <img
                src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/688660/pexels-photo-688660.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800"
                alt="Cold wave preparedness"
              />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="readiness-slide" id="slide-flood">
            <div class="readiness-content">
              <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-water"></i> Get Ready for Floods</h3>
              <p>
                Floods can come quickly after heavy rain or dam release.
                Planning now helps you react calmly and safely.
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Identify safe higher places and nearest shelters.</li>
                <li>Keep important documents in waterproof pouches.</li>
                <li>Prepare a small emergency “go-bag” with essentials.</li>
              </ul>
              <button
                type="button"
                class="btn btn-outline read-more-toggle"
                data-target="floodMore"
              >
                Read more
              </button>
              <div class="read-more-content" id="floodMore">
                <p>
                  • Never ignore early flood warnings or evacuation messages.<br />
                  • Keep a battery-powered radio or fully charged phone for alerts.<br />
                  • Turn off electricity and gas at main switches if instructed by authorities.<br />
                  • Teach children basic safety rules: “Don’t play in flood water” and “Stay with adults”.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="readiness-image-box">
              <!-- Flood image -->
