    <!-- RESPONSE GUIDELINES -->
    <section id="response">
      <div class="section-card response-main-card">
        <div class="section-header">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-helmet-safety"></i>
          <h2>Disaster Response Guidelines</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          Follow these basic guidelines during common emergencies. Share them with
          your family and neighbours so everyone knows what to do.
        </p>

        <div class="cards">
          <div class="response-card">
            <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-house-crack"></i> Earthquake</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Indoors:</strong> Drop, Cover, and Hold On under a strong table.</li>
              <li>Stay away from windows, glass, and heavy furniture.</li>
              <li>Do not use lifts; use stairs after shaking stops.</li>
              <li>Move to open ground away from buildings once safe.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="response-card">
            <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-water"></i> Flood</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Move to higher ground immediately; avoid low-lying areas.</li>
              <li>Do not walk or drive through moving flood water.</li>
              <li>Turn off electricity and gas if instructed and safe.</li>
              <li>Keep drinking water, dry food and important documents sealed.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="response-card">
            <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-fire-flame-curved"></i> Fire</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Raise an alarm and call the fire department immediately.</li>
              <li>Use stairs, never lifts, during evacuation.</li>
              <li>Crawl low under smoke to avoid inhalation.</li>
              <li>If clothes catch fire: Stop, Drop, and Roll.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="quick-note">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-triangle-exclamation"></i>
          <p>
            <strong>Quick Checklist:</strong><br />
            Keep a basic emergency kit ready (torch, first aid, power bank, whistle, important
            documents). Save emergency numbers and practice mock drills with your family at
            least twice a year.
          </p>
        </div>

